"releaseNotes":"* Improved phone number matching for more reliable updates\n* Better review flow before applying changes\n* Select individual numbers before saving\n* Added Select All / Deselect All controls\n* Added an option to include or exclude work/business numbers\n* Stronger normalization rules to avoid changing malformed numbers\n* Better handling for extensions and edge cases\n* Clearer results summary after changes are applied\n* Improved reporting for phone numbers updated vs. contacts updated\n* General UI polish and stability improvements", "version":"1.1", "wrapperType":"software", "currency":"USD", 
"description":"ContactFixer solves a small but annoying problem: your iPhone contacts are a mix of formats. Some numbers have the +1 country code, some have area codes in parentheses, some are just ten raw digits. iMessage, FaceTime, and third-party apps all behave better when numbers are in a consistent E.164 format — and ContactFixer gets you there in seconds.\n\nHOW IT WORKS\nTap Scan Contacts and ContactFixer reads through your entire contacts list, identifying every US phone number missing the +1 country code. It shows you a full preview — contact name, old number, and new number — before changing anything. When you're ready, tap Apply All Changes and every contact is updated instantly using Apple's native Contacts framework.\n\nWHAT GETS FIXED\n(708) 555-0142 → +17085550142\n312-555-0198 → +13125550198\n8005550167 → +18005550167\n17085550031 → +17085550031\n\nNumbers already beginning with + are never touched. Your international contacts stay exactly as they are.\n\nCOMPLETELY PRIVATE\nContactFixer has no backend, no account, no analytics, and no ads. It makes zero network requests — you can run it in airplane mode and it works identically. Your contacts are read and written using the same native framework Apple's own Contacts app uses. Nothing ever leaves your device.\n\nSIMPLE BY DESIGN\nThere's nothing to configure. No settings, no subscriptions, no account to create. Scan, review, apply — done.", "languageCodesISO2A":[], "averageUserRatingForCurrentVersion":0, "fileSizeBytes":"1465344", "formattedPrice":"Free", "minimumOsVersion":"16.0", "price":0.00, "userRatingCount":0}, 
