"releaseNotes":"* Added official NOAA / National Weather Service alerts\n* Improved local awareness for weather warnings and hazards near you\n* Default dashboard sorting now opens on Nearest\n* Improved map styling so ISS is visually distinct from flood events\n* Clarified wildfire data sources so FIRMS hotspot detections and EONET regional wildfire context are easier to understand\n* Refined app structure and internal organization for better stability and future updates\n* Cleaned up event categorization across live sky items, alerts, and event cards\n* Improved settings and app metadata handling\n* General bug fixes and UI polish", "version":"1.1", "wrapperType":"software", "currency":"USD", 
"description":"Here's a full App Store description, punchy opening, feature breakdown, data sources, and a strong close:\n\nThe Earth never stops moving.\nEarthquakes ripple through the crust. Solar flares erupt from the Sun. The ISS streaks overhead at 28,000 km/h. Wildfires ignite from satellite-detected heat. The aurora dances at the edge of the atmosphere.\nTremula monitors all of it — and puts it in your pocket, live.\nWhat Tremula tracks:\n\nEARTHQUAKES\nReal-time seismic data from the USGS Earthquake Hazards Program. See every significant earthquake globally and every tremor near you, with magnitude, depth, and exact location — within minutes of it happening.\n\nAURORA BOREALIS\nLive Kp index from NOAA's Space Weather Prediction Center, updated every 3 hours. Know whether tonight is a 0 or a 9, and whether the northern lights might be visible from your backyard.\n\nINTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION\nReal-time ISS position, updated live on an interactive map. Watch it move. See how far it is from you, what region it's flying over, and how long until it comes back around.\n\nASTEROIDS & METEORS\nDaily close approach data from NASA's Near Earth Object program, calibrated in lunar distances so you actually understand the scale. Plus the full annual meteor shower calendar — loaded offline, always ready.\n\nWILDFIRES\nDual coverage from NASA FIRMS satellite thermal detection and NASA EONET curated events. See active fires near you with precise coordinates, straight from orbital infrared sensors.\n\nFLOODS\nUSGS stream gauge readings near your location. When a river hits flood stage, you'll know before it makes the news.\n\nSOLAR FLARES & SPACE WEATHER\nX-class and M-class solar flares from NASA DONKI, plus coronal mass ejections headed toward Earth. When a fast CME launches, Tremula tells you aurora enhancement is coming in 1–3 days.\n\nASTRONOMY PICTURE OF THE DAY\nNASA's daily image of the universe — a stunning reminder of the scale of everything.\n\nBuilt on data you can trust:\nEvery number in Tremula comes from a government-maintained scientific source — USGS, NOAA, NASA. No scraped websites. No third-party aggregators. No paywalled data resold to you. Just the raw feed, beautifully presented.\n\nDesigned for real life:\nTremula works offline. The last known data is always cached, so you're never left with a blank screen. Pull to refresh anytime. Automatic background refresh keeps things current even when the app is closed.\n\nLocation is used only to surface events near you — nearby earthquakes, local wildfire detection, aurora visibility at your latitude. Your coordinates go directly from your device to government APIs. We never see them, store them, or share them.\n\nBeautiful on every device:\nDark, cosmic interface designed for night-time use. Full iPad support with a two-column layout and a live global map. Tappable filter tiles. Haptic feedback. A real-time ISS tracker that moves while you watch.", "languageCodesISO2A":["EN"], "averageUserRatingForCurrentVersion":0, "fileSizeBytes":"3238912", "formattedPrice":"Free", "minimumOsVersion":"17.0", "price":0.00, "userRatingCount":0}]
